Babina Noko, popularly known as Sekhukhune United, has parted ways with co-coach, Owen “Thifuriwi” Da Gama. Da Gama joined Babina Noko in April this year as co-coach to MacDonald Makhubedu for the remainder of the 2021/22 DSTV Premiership. The club is currently sitting on number 11 in the PSL. The club said they would like to wish Da Gama all the best. For the latest sports news from Sunday World, click here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here